originContent: # Jib
translatedContent: # Jib

originContent: *A Julia implementation of Interactive Brokers API*
translatedContent: *Una implementación en Julia de la API de Interactive Brokers*

originContent: `Jib` is a native [Julia](https://julialang.org/) client that implements
translatedContent: `Jib` es un cliente nativo de [Julia](https://julialang.org/) que implementa

originContent: [Interactive Brokers](https://www.interactivebrokers.com/) API to communicate
translatedContent: la API de [Interactive Brokers](https://www.interactivebrokers.com/) para comunicarse

originContent: with TWS or IBGateway.
translatedContent: con TWS o IBGateway.

originContent: It aims to be feature complete, however it does not support legacy versions.
translatedContent: Su objetivo es ser completo en cuanto a funcionalidades, sin embargo no soporta versiones antiguas.

originContent: It is noteworthy to mention that the official IB API has recently adopted
translatedContent: Cabe mencionar que la API oficial de IB ha adoptado recientemente

originContent: Protocol Buffers as the underlying wire format, replacing the legacy custom protocol.
translatedContent: Protocol Buffers como formato de transmisión, reemplazando el protocolo personalizado legado.

originContent: This package followed suit and support for the latter has been dropped.
translatedContent: Este paquete siguió la misma línea y se eliminó el soporte para el anterior.

originContent: Currently, only API versions `v213+` are supported, which translates to
translatedContent: Actualmente, sólo se soportan versiones de API `v213+`, lo que equivale a

originContent: TWS version `10.40` or later.
translatedContent: la versión `10.40` de TWS o superior.

originContent: The package design follows the official C++/Java
translatedContent: El diseño del paquete sigue la API oficial en C++/Java

originContent: [IB API](https://interactivebrokers.github.io/tws-api/),
translatedContent: [IB API](https://interactivebrokers.github.io/tws-api/),

originContent: which is based on an asynchronous communication model over TCP.
translatedContent: que se basa en un modelo de comunicación asíncrono sobre TCP.

originContent: ## Usage
translatedContent: ## Uso

originContent: The user interacts mainly with these two objects:
translatedContent: El usuario interactúa principalmente con estos dos objetos:

originContent: - `Connection`: a handle holding a connection to the server
translatedContent: - `Connection`: un manejador que mantiene una conexión con el servidor

originContent: - `Wrapper`: a container for the callbacks that are invoked
translatedContent: - `Wrapper`: un contenedor para los callbacks que se invocan

originContent: when the server responses are processed.
translatedContent: cuando se procesan las respuestas del servidor.

originContent: Other data structures, such as `Contract` and `Order`, are implemented as Julia `struct`
translatedContent: Otras estructuras de datos, como `Contract` y `Order`, están implementadas como `struct` de Julia

originContent: and mirror the respective classes in the official IB API.
translatedContent: y reflejan las respectivas clases en la API oficial de IB.

originContent: A complete minimal working example is shown.
translatedContent: Se muestra un ejemplo mínimo completo y funcional.

originContent: For this code to work, an instance of IB TWS or IBGateway needs to be running
translatedContent: Para que este código funcione, debe estar ejecutándose una instancia de IB TWS o IBGateway

originContent: on the local machine and listening on port `4002`.
translatedContent: en la máquina local y escuchando en el puerto `4002`.

originContent: **Note:** _demo_ or _paper_ account recommended!! :smirk:
translatedContent: **Nota:** _cuenta demo_ o _cuenta paper_ recomendada!! :smirk:

originContent: ```julia
translatedContent: ```julia

originContent: using Jib
translatedContent: using Jib

originContent: wrap = Jib.Wrapper(
translatedContent: wrap = Jib.Wrapper(

originContent: # Customized methods go here
translatedContent: # Customized methods go here

originContent: error= (id, errorTime, errorCode, errorString, advancedOrderRejectJson) ->
translatedContent: error= (id, errorTime, errorCode, errorString, advancedOrderRejectJson) ->

originContent: println("Error: $(something(id, "NA")) $errorTime $errorCode $errorString $advancedOrderRejectJson"),
translatedContent: println("Error: $(something(id, "NA")) $errorTime $errorCode $errorString $advancedOrderRejectJson"),

originContent: nextValidId= (orderId) -> println("Next OrderId: $orderId"),
translatedContent: nextValidId= (orderId) -> println("Next OrderId: $orderId"),

translatedContent: managedAccounts= (accountsList) -> println("Managed Accounts: $accountsList")

originContent: # more method overrides can go here...
translatedContent: # more method overrides can go here...

translatedContent: # Connect to the server with clientId = 1

translatedContent: ib = Jib.connect(4002, 1);

translatedContent: # Start a background Task to process the server responses

translatedContent: Jib.start_reader(ib, wrap);

translatedContent: contract = Jib.Contract(symbol="GOOG",

originContent: #### Foreground vs. Background Processing
translatedContent: #### Procesamiento en primer plano vs. segundo plano

originContent: It is possible to process the server responses either within the main process
translatedContent: Es posible procesar las respuestas del servidor ya sea dentro del proceso principal

originContent: or in a separate background `Task`:
translatedContent: o en una `Task` separada en segundo plano:

originContent: - **foreground processing** is triggered by invoking `Jib.check_all(ib, wrap)`.
translatedContent: - **procesamiento en primer plano** se activa invocando `Jib.check_all(ib, wrap)`.

originContent: It is the user's responsibility to call it on a **regular basis**,
translatedContent: Es responsabilidad del usuario llamarlo de forma **regular**,

originContent: especially when data are streaming in.
translatedContent: especialmente cuando los datos están llegando en streaming.

originContent: - **background processing** is started by `Jib.start_reader(ib, wrap)`.
translatedContent: - **procesamiento en segundo plano** se inicia con `Jib.start_reader(ib, wrap)`.

originContent: A separate `Task` is started in the background, which monitors the connection and processes
translatedContent: Se inicia una `Task` separada en segundo plano, que monitorea la conexión y procesa

originContent: the responses as they arrive.
translatedContent: las respuestas a medida que llegan.

originContent: To avoid undesired effects, the two approaches should not be mixed together
translatedContent: Para evitar efectos no deseados, no se deben mezclar ambos enfoques

originContent: on the same connection.
translatedContent: en la misma conexión.

originContent: ## Implementation Details
translatedContent: ## Detalles de Implementación

originContent: The package does not export any name, therefore any functions
translatedContent: El paquete no exporta ningún nombre, por lo que cualquier función

originContent: or types described here need to be prefixed by `Jib.*`.
translatedContent: o tipo descrito aquí necesita ser prefijado con `Jib.*`.

originContent: As Julia is not an object-oriented language, the functionality of the IB
translatedContent: Como Julia no es un lenguaje orientado a objetos, la funcionalidad del IB

originContent: `EClient` class is provided here by regular functions. In particular:
translatedContent: `EClient` se provee aquí mediante funciones regulares. En particular:

originContent: - `connect(port, clientId, connectOptions)`: establish a connection and return
translatedContent: - `connect(port, clientId, connectOptions)`: establece una conexión y devuelve

originContent: a `Connection` object.
translatedContent: un objeto `Connection`.

originContent: - `disconnect(::Connection)`: terminate the connection.
translatedContent: - `disconnect(::Connection)`: termina la conexión.

originContent: - `check_all(::Connection, ::Wrapper)`: process available responses, **not blocking**.
translatedContent: - `check_all(::Connection, ::Wrapper)`: procesa respuestas disponibles, **sin bloqueo**.

originContent: Return the number of messages processed. **Needs to be called regularly!**
translatedContent: Devuelve el número de mensajes procesados. **¡Debe llamarse regularmente!**

originContent: - `start_reader(::Connection, ::Wrapper)`: start a `Task` for background processing.
translatedContent: - `start_reader(::Connection, ::Wrapper)`: inicia una `Task` para procesamiento en segundo plano.

originContent: - methods that send specific requests to the server.
translatedContent: - métodos que envían solicitudes específicas al servidor.

originContent: Refer to the official IB `EClient` class documentation for further details and method signatures.
translatedContent: Consulte la documentación oficial de la clase IB `EClient` para más detalles y firmas de métodos.

originContent: The only caveat is to remember to pass a `Connection` as first argument: _e.g._
translatedContent: La única salvedad es recordar pasar un `Connection` como primer argumento: _p.ej._

originContent: `reqContractDetails(ib::Connection, reqId:Int, contract::Contract)`
translatedContent: `reqContractDetails(ib::Connection, reqId:Int, contract::Contract)`

originContent: #### [`Wrapper`](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/src/wrapper.jl)
translatedContent: #### [`Wrapper`](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/src/wrapper.jl)

originContent: Like the official IB `EWrapper` class, this `struct` holds the callbacks
translatedContent: Al igual que la clase oficial IB `EWrapper`, este `struct` contiene los callbacks

originContent: that are dispatched when responses are processed.
translatedContent: que se despachan cuando se procesan las respuestas.

originContent: The user provides the callback definitions as keyword arguments
translatedContent: El usuario provee las definiciones de los callbacks como argumentos clave

originContent: in the constructor, as shown [above](#usage), and/or by setting
translatedContent: en el constructor, como se mostró [arriba](#usage), y/o configurando

originContent: the property of an existing instance.
translatedContent: la propiedad de una instancia existente.

originContent: A more comprehensive example is provided by [`simple_wrap()`](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/src/wrapper.jl#L130),
translatedContent: Un ejemplo más completo se provee en [`simple_wrap()`](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/src/wrapper.jl#L130),

originContent: which is used like this:
translatedContent: que se utiliza así:

originContent: ```julia
translatedContent: ```julia

originContent: using Jib: Jib, Contract, reqContractDetails, simple_wrap, start_reader
translatedContent: using Jib: Jib, Contract, reqContractDetails, simple_wrap, start_reader

originContent: data, wrap = simple_wrap();
translatedContent: data, wrap = simple_wrap();

originContent: ib = Jib.connect(4002, 1);
translatedContent: ib = Jib.connect(4002, 1);

originContent: start_reader(ib, wrap);
translatedContent: start_reader(ib, wrap);

originContent: reqContractDetails(ib, 99, Contract(conId=208813720, exchange="SMART"))
translatedContent: reqContractDetails(ib, 99, Contract(conId=208813720, exchange="SMART"))

originContent: # Wait for the response and then access the "ContractDetails" result:
translatedContent: # Wait for the response and then access the "ContractDetails" result:

originContent: data[:cd]
translatedContent: data[:cd]

originContent: Thanks to closures, `data` (a `Dict` in this case) is accessible by all
translatedContent: Gracias a los cierres (closures), `data` (un `Dict` en este caso) es accesible por todos

originContent: `wrap` methods as well as the main program. This is one way to
translatedContent: los métodos `wrap` así como por el programa principal. Esta es una forma de

originContent: propagate incoming data to different parts of the program.
translatedContent: propagar datos entrantes a diferentes partes del programa.

originContent: For more details about callback definitions and signatures,
translatedContent: Para más detalles sobre las definiciones y firmas de callbacks,

originContent: refer to the official IB `EWrapper` class documentation.
translatedContent: consulte la documentación oficial de la clase `EWrapper` de IB.

originContent: As reference, the exact signatures used in this package
translatedContent: Como referencia, las firmas exactas usadas en este paquete

originContent: are found [here](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/data/wrapper_signatures.jl).
translatedContent: se encuentran [aquí](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lbilli/Jib.jl/master/data/wrapper_signatures.jl).

originContent: ## Notes
translatedContent: ## Notas

originContent: Callbacks are generally invoked with arguments and types matching the signatures
translatedContent: Los callbacks generalmente se invocan con argumentos y tipos que coinciden con las firmas

originContent: as described in the official documentation.
translatedContent: descritas en la documentación oficial.

originContent: However, there are few exceptions:
translatedContent: Sin embargo, hay pocas excepciones:

originContent: - `tickPrice()` has an extra `size::Float64` argument,
translatedContent: - `tickPrice()` tiene un argumento extra `size::Float64`,

originContent: which is meaningful only when `TickType ∈ {BID, ASK, LAST}`.
translatedContent: que tiene sentido solo cuando `TickType ∈ {BID, ASK, LAST}`.

originContent: In these cases, the official IB API fires an extra `tickSize()` event instead.
translatedContent: En estos casos, la API oficial de IB dispara un evento extra `tickSize()` en su lugar.

originContent: - `historicalData()` is invoked only once per request,
translatedContent: - `historicalData()` se invoca solo una vez por solicitud,

originContent: presenting all the historical data as a single `Vector{Bar}`,
translatedContent: presentando todos los datos históricos como un único `Vector{Bar}`,

originContent: whereas the official IB API invokes it row-by-row.
translatedContent: mientras que la API oficial de IB lo invoca fila por fila.

originContent: - `scannerData()` is similarly invoked once per request with a `Vector{ScannerDataElement}`
translatedContent: - `scannerData()` se invoca de manera similar una vez por solicitud con un `Vector{ScannerDataElement}`

originContent: as argument. Consequently, `scannerDataEnd()` is redundant and
translatedContent: como argumento. En consecuencia, `scannerDataEnd()` es redundante y

originContent: it is **not** used in this package.
translatedContent: **no** se usa en este paquete.

originContent: These modifications make it possible to establish the rule:
translatedContent: Estas modificaciones hacen posible establecer la regla:

originContent: _one callback per server response_.
translatedContent: _un callback por respuesta del servidor_.

originContent: #### Missing Values
translatedContent: #### Valores faltantes

originContent: Occasionally, for numerical types, there is the need to represent
translatedContent: Ocasionalmente, para tipos numéricos, existe la necesidad de representar

originContent: the lack of a value.
translatedContent: la falta de un valor.

originContent: IB API does not have a uniform solution across the board, but rather
translatedContent: La API de IB no tiene una solución uniforme en todos los casos, sino que

originContent: it adopts a variety of sentinel values.
translatedContent: adopta una variedad de valores centinela.

originContent: They can be either the plain `0` or the largest representable value
translatedContent: Estos pueden ser el simple `0` o el valor representable más grande

originContent: for 32- and 64-bit integers respectively or `1.7976931348623157E308`
translatedContent: para enteros de 32 y 64 bits respectivamente o `1.7976931348623157E308`

originContent: for 64-bit floating point.
translatedContent: para punto flotante de 64 bits.

originContent: This package makes an effort to use Julia built-in `Nothing`
translatedContent: Este paquete hace un esfuerzo para usar `Nothing` incorporado en Julia

originContent: in all circumstances.
translatedContent: en todas las circunstancias.

translatedContent: tipos y valores predeterminados que coinciden con sus equivalentes en la API de IB: _p. ej._

translatedContent: `Contract`, `Order`, `ComboLeg`, `ExecutionFilter`, `ScannerSubscription`
